The state has stopped a university student from travelling to India for a kidney transplant. The Ministry of Health said such services are available in Kenya and there is no need of Kenneth Kinyua to go abroad. The Information Technology student at Mt Kenya University was diagnosed with stage five kidney failure last year. He has been undergoing three dialysis sessions every week The 24-year-old is underweight. He was 65kg in August, 2017, but now weighs 30kg. "He underwent three surgeries last year, I think this caused to his kidneys to fail," guardian John Kandia said. Kinyua comes from Kangari village of Runyenjes constituency in Embu county.